  <h2>What Comes Into Play</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Hose distance.</strong> Vacuum hoses have practical limits from truck to tank.</li>
    <li><strong>Slopes and rock.</strong> Plateau terrain affects access and system design.</li>
    <li><strong>Soft ground.</strong> River-valley and spring conditions can complicate truck access.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Planning Around It</h2>
  <p>
    Noting your access realities in a service request helps a provider come prepared. For regional planning, see <a href="/resources/upper-cumberland-septic-guide/">the Upper Cumberland guide</a>, or <a href="/request-service/">request septic service</a>.
  </p>

